lirubin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'The use of bedaquiline with other potentially hepatotoxic agents should be avoided whenever possible (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/54842/', '', 'Capreomycin, Rifamycin, Streptomycin, Trimethoprim, Cycloserine, Pyridoxine, Pretomanid', 'Brivaracetam, Topiramate, Lamotrigine, Ethosuximide, Lacosamide, Levetiracetam, Tiagabine, Clonazepam, Paramethadione, Perampanel, Ganaxolone, More', 1767369485);
